                            <comment id="13894267" author="daijy" created="Fri, 7 Feb 2014 07:36:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Instruction for test environment:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Install cygwin 1.7.28+ (earlier version has a bug), minimum core + perl, dev module&lt;br/&gt;
2. Install perl module (Parallel::ForkManager, IPC::Run)&lt;br/&gt;
To install it, open a cygwin terminal, use &quot;cpan Parallel::ForkManager&quot; etc to install.&lt;br/&gt;
3. Need to put $CYGWIN_HOME/bin in PATH, after GnuWin32. Test will pick perl from cygwin, every other utilities still from GnuWin32.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14011216" author="arpitgupta" created="Wed, 28 May 2014 16:40:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 we have been running tests in parallel on windows with this patch and have found no regressions in the framework.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
